column1: text
Panic disorder: symptoms include anxiety, chest pain, shortness of breath.
Depression: symptoms include insomnia, anxiety, fatigue.
Asthma: symptoms include shortness of breath, cough.
Diabetes: symptoms include frequent urination, excessive thirst, fatigue.
Hypertension: symptoms include headache, dizziness, blurred vision.
Anemia: symptoms include fatigue, weakness, pale skin.
Pneumonia: symptoms include fever, cough, chest pain.
Migraine: symptoms include severe headache, nausea, light sensitivity.
Anxiety disorder: symptoms include excessive worry, restlessness, fatigue.
Chronic bronchitis: symptoms include chronic cough, mucus production, wheezing.
Emphysema: symptoms include shortness of breath, chronic cough, fatigue.
Heart attack: symptoms include chest pain, shortness of breath, nausea.
Heart failure: symptoms include swelling, shortness of breath, fatigue.
Arrhythmia: symptoms include irregular heartbeat, dizziness, chest discomfort.
Stroke: symptoms include facial drooping, arm weakness, speech difficulty.
Epilepsy: symptoms include seizures, confusion, loss of consciousness.
Alzheimer’s disease: symptoms include memory loss, confusion, mood changes.
Parkinson’s disease: symptoms include tremor, stiffness, slow movement.
Multiple sclerosis: symptoms include vision problems, weakness, coordination issues.
Rheumatoid arthritis: symptoms include joint pain, swelling, stiffness.
Osteoarthritis: symptoms include joint pain, stiffness, limited mobility.
Osteoporosis: symptoms include bone weakness, fractures, back pain.
Gout: symptoms include sudden joint pain, swelling, redness.
Lupus: symptoms include fatigue, joint pain, skin rash.
Fibromyalgia: symptoms include widespread pain, fatigue, sleep problems.
Chronic fatigue syndrome: symptoms include extreme fatigue, poor concentration, headaches.
Irritable bowel syndrome: symptoms include abdominal pain, bloating, diarrhea.
Crohn’s disease: symptoms include diarrhea, abdominal pain, weight loss.
Ulcerative colitis: symptoms include bloody diarrhea, abdominal cramps, fatigue.
Gastritis: symptoms include stomach pain, nausea, vomiting.
Peptic ulcer disease: symptoms include burning stomach pain, bloating, heartburn.
GERD: symptoms include heartburn, chest pain, regurgitation.
Hepatitis: symptoms include jaundice, fatigue, abdominal pain.
Liver cirrhosis: symptoms include swelling, fatigue, jaundice.
Pancreatitis: symptoms include severe abdominal pain, nausea, vomiting.
Gallstones: symptoms include upper abdominal pain, nausea, indigestion.
Kidney stones: symptoms include severe flank pain, blood in urine, nausea.
Chronic kidney disease: symptoms include fatigue, swelling, changes in urination.
Urinary tract infection: symptoms include painful urination, frequent urination, urgency.
Bladder infection: symptoms include pelvic pain, burning urination, cloudy urine.
Prostate enlargement: symptoms include weak urine stream, frequent urination, urgency.
Erectile dysfunction: symptoms include difficulty maintaining erection, reduced libido.
Polycystic ovary syndrome: symptoms include irregular periods, acne, weight gain.
Endometriosis: symptoms include pelvic pain, painful periods, infertility.
Menopause: symptoms include hot flashes, mood changes, night sweats.
Hypothyroidism: symptoms include weight gain, fatigue, cold intolerance.
Hyperthyroidism: symptoms include weight loss, anxiety, rapid heartbeat.
Goiter: symptoms include neck swelling, hoarseness, difficulty swallowing.
Obesity: symptoms include excessive body weight, fatigue, joint pain.
Metabolic syndrome: symptoms include high blood pressure, high blood sugar, obesity.
Vitamin D deficiency: symptoms include bone pain, muscle weakness, fatigue.
Vitamin B12 deficiency: symptoms include numbness, fatigue, memory problems.
Scurvy: symptoms include bleeding gums, weakness, bruising.
Seasonal allergies: symptoms include sneezing, runny nose, itchy eyes.
Food allergy: symptoms include hives, swelling, nausea.
Eczema: symptoms include itchy skin, redness, dryness.
Psoriasis: symptoms include scaly skin patches, itching, joint pain.
Acne: symptoms include pimples, oily skin, inflammation.
Rosacea: symptoms include facial redness, flushing, visible blood vessels.
Skin cancer: symptoms include changing moles, skin lesions, bleeding.
Melanoma: symptoms include irregular mole shape, color changes, itching.
Conjunctivitis: symptoms include red eyes, itching, discharge.
Cataracts: symptoms include blurred vision, glare sensitivity, cloudy vision.
Glaucoma: symptoms include eye pain, vision loss, headaches.
Macular degeneration: symptoms include central vision loss, blurred vision.
Otitis media: symptoms include ear pain, fever, hearing loss.
Tinnitus: symptoms include ringing ears, buzzing sounds, hearing difficulty.
Sinusitis: symptoms include facial pain, nasal congestion, headache.
Common cold: symptoms include sneezing, sore throat, runny nose.
Influenza: symptoms include fever, muscle aches, fatigue.
COVID-19: symptoms include fever, cough, loss of taste.
Tuberculosis: symptoms include chronic cough, weight loss, night sweats.
Mononucleosis: symptoms include sore throat, fever, swollen lymph nodes.
HIV infection: symptoms include fever, fatigue, swollen glands.
AIDS: symptoms include severe infections, weight loss, chronic fatigue.
Sepsis: symptoms include fever, rapid heartbeat, confusion.
Leukemia: symptoms include fatigue, frequent infections, bruising.
Lymphoma: symptoms include swollen lymph nodes, fever, night sweats.
Breast cancer: symptoms include breast lump, pain, nipple discharge.
Lung cancer: symptoms include chronic cough, chest pain, weight loss.
Colon cancer: symptoms include blood in stool, abdominal pain, anemia.
Prostate cancer: symptoms include urinary issues, bone pain, weight loss.
